<paragraph blockId="22.[831,1437,726,976]" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,964,726,749]" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">Comments:</emphasis>
This species appears closely related with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2015" box="[831,949,758,781]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequum">
<emphasis box="[831,949,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">S. aequum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both possess metaventrite with a median groove and a pair of foveiform impressions, and have similar aedeagi. These species may be easily distinguished by their colour pattern. In addition, the groove of the metaventrite is shorter, the elytral punctation finer, and the apical process of the median lobe is abruptly narrowed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2015" box="[1062,1167,953,976]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aereum">
<emphasis box="[1062,1167,953,976]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">S. aereum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
